      <div class="gp-pricing-context">
        <p class="gp-context-paragraph">Google Pixel repair costs vary significantly by model and generation — a Pixel 3a screen is considerably less expensive to repair than a Pixel 9 Pro XL with its LTPO OLED display, and Pixel Fold devices are among the most complex and costly foldable repairs available. <a href="https://support.google.com/pixelphone/answer/7173610" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="gp-context-link">Google's own repair documentation</a> outlines what to expect from out-of-warranty Pixel repairs.</p>
        <p class="gp-context-paragraph">Many customers are surprised that Pixel Pro and Fold repairs approach the cost of newer Pixel a-series devices. <a href="https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/google" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="gp-context-link">iFixit's Pixel repairability scores</a> show why certain models are easier to repair than others — the Pixel 6a and 7a score significantly higher than Pro models due to their simpler display assemblies and easier battery access.</p>
        <p class="gp-context-paragraph">If the repair cost doesn't make financial sense for your Pixel model's current value, we'll walk you through the options honestly — including trade-in value toward a newer Pixel or a refurbished device from our pre-owned inventory.</p>
