  <section class="gp-faq-section" id="faqs">
    <div class="gp-container">
      <div class="gp-section-header">
        <h2 class="gp-section-title">Google Pixel Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="gp-section-subtitle">Common questions about Google Pixel repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gp-faq-list">
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>How long does Google Pixel screen replacement take in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">Most Pixel screen replacements are completed within 1–2 hours at our Winnipeg St. Vital location. Pixel Fold and Pixel 9 Pro Fold devices require 2–4 hours due to their complex folding display assemblies and hinge mechanisms.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Pixel Fold and Pixel 9 Pro Fold in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">Yes — we specialise in Pixel Fold and Pixel 9 Pro Fold repairs including inner screen, outer screen, hinge mechanism, and flex cable issues. Foldable screen repairs are among the most complex phone repairs available — contact us to confirm parts availability and get a quote before visiting.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>Will my Pixel still receive software updates after repair?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">Yes — your Pixel will continue receiving all Google software updates, security patches, and Pixel Feature Drops after our repair. Our repairs are hardware-only and do not affect the Android OS, Google services, or any software functionality on your device.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>How much does Google Pixel repair cost in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">Pixel repair costs vary by model and repair type — Pixel a-series repairs are typically the most affordable, while Pro models and Fold devices cost more due to premium OLED and LTPO display components. Contact us or use our online quote tool for a free upfront price on your specific model.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>Do Pixel repairs affect camera quality or AI features?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">No — our repairs preserve all of your Pixel's AI photography features including Night Sight, Magic Eraser, Photo Unblur, and computational zoom. We use quality parts that maintain the hardware specifications required for Pixel's camera software to function correctly.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Google Pixel batteries in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">Yes — same-day Pixel battery replacement is available for all models at our Winnipeg St. Vital location. Pixel batteries typically degrade noticeably after 2–3 years and a replacement can restore full Adaptive Battery life — all battery replacements include a 90-day warranty.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix a Google Pixel that won't turn on?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">Yes — a non-responsive Pixel is often caused by a depleted battery, a failed display connection, or a software boot issue. We run free diagnostics to identify the root cause before recommending any repair so you know exactly what the problem is before spending anything.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Pixel under-display fingerprint sensors?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">Yes — we repair and recalibrate under-display optical fingerprint sensors on Pixel 6, 7, 8, and 9 series devices. Fingerprint sensor issues often occur after screen replacements that use incompatible panels — we use model-matched screens to prevent this.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>Do I need an appointment for Pixel repair in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">No appointment is needed — walk-ins are welcome at both our St. Vital and Thompson locations during business hours. Calling ahead is helpful for Pixel Fold or Pro model repairs so we can confirm we have your specific parts in stock before your visit.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="gp-faq-item">
          <summary class="gp-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Google Pixel phones in Thompson, MB?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="gp-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="gp-faq-answer">Yes — our Thompson location at 300 Mystery Lake Rd #1530 accepts Pixel repairs and walk-ins Monday through Saturday 10AM–6PM. We stock parts for common Pixel models — calling ahead helps confirm availability for newer or Pro models.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

